Weapons (Heavy / Siege Hardpoints – Capital Only)

HAG-MK16A “Gram” — 130mm Artillery Cannon (L1)

Damage: 75 – 135 (upgrades)
Armor Piercing: 35
Range: 2300 – 4000 m (upgrades)
Optimal Range: 2750 m (upgrades)
Accuracy: 125
Critical Offense: 100
Reload: 8 s
Power Cost: 64
Firing Arc: 35°
Cost: 500 000
Durability: 20 000 / 20 000

Effect:
High-caliber artillery cannon for Capital-class vessels.
Delivers devastating long-range firepower designed for siege and ship-of-the-line engagements.
Extremely limited firing arc and long reload, balanced by immense per-shot impact and armor penetration.
Incapable of reliably hitting Strike-class ships due to target size and slow traverse.

Upgrade Model:
Increase Damage and Optimal Range per level. Reload and Power Cost remain fixed unless higher-level data show changes.

Implementation Notes:

Uses standard ballistic and crit formulas; apply standard falloff from Optimal Range (peak DPS ≈ 2750 m).

Designed for broadside or fixed forward mounts — do not allow 360° traversal.

Each shot consumes full Power Cost at the moment of firing.

Accuracy tuned for large, slow targets (Line or Capital classes).

Minimum effective range (≈ 2300 m) prevents close-range use; enforce via targeting logic.

Restricted to Capital-class hardpoints — enforce requirement in Store and Fitting UI.

Consider adding screen-shake and concussive sound effects for cinematic impact.

Weapons (Defensive / Support Hardpoints – Capital Only)

PD-X30P “Wildfire” — 25mm Point Defense Battery (L1)

Damage: 3 – 7 (upgrades)
Armor Piercing: 5
Range: 0 – 1200 m (upgrades)
Optimal Range: 500 m (upgrades)
Accuracy: 500
Critical Offense: 100
Reload: 0.5 s
Power Cost: 3.5
Firing Arc: 180°
Cost: 300 000
Durability: 25 000 / 25 000

Effect:
Automated close-in defensive weapon system for Capital-class ships.
Provides rapid-response interception against incoming missiles, strike craft, and torpedoes.
Extremely high rate of fire and accuracy make it ideal for layered point defense at close range.
Poor performance against heavily armored or distant targets.

Upgrade Model:
Increase Damage and Range per level. Reload and Power Cost remain fixed unless higher-level data indicate changes.

Implementation Notes:

Functions as a CIWS (Close-In Weapon System) with automatic engagement capability.

Should prioritize hostile missiles, drones, and small ships within 1 km.

Uses projectile-based logic; apply hit rolls per shot with standard accuracy formula.

Accuracy 500 ensures reliable tracking at short range.

Low Armor Piercing prevents meaningful hull damage to Line or Capital ships.

Restricted to Capital-class defensive hardpoints — enforce eligibility in Store and Fitting UI.

Consider adding continuous tracer fire and tracking audio cues for visual clarity.

