M-37A “Fusillade” — 6.3mm Spot Flak (L1)

Damage: 20 – 30 (upgrades)
Armor Piercing: 15
Range: 1000 – 1400 m (upgrades)
Optimal Range: 1200 m (upgrades)
Accuracy: 300
Critical Offense: 100
Reload: 1 s
Power Cost: 5
Firing Arc: 45°
Cost: 450 000
Durability: 25 000 / 25 000

Effect:
Short-arc defensive flak cannon designed for Capital-class ships.
Fires directed explosive shells that detonate near incoming threats within a narrow arc.
Highly effective at intercepting missiles and small craft in a defined coverage zone.
Combines concentrated damage bursts with limited field of fire — best used in coordinated flak grids.

Upgrade Model:
Increase Damage and Range per level. Reload and Power Cost remain fixed unless higher-level data indicate otherwise.

Implementation Notes:

Uses proximity detonation model with small explosive radius (≈10–20 m).

Moderate Armor Piercing allows it to damage lightly armored ships but remains defensive in intent.

Accuracy 300 reflects area saturation rather than precision targeting.

Power Cost applied per volley; independent reloads per turret.

Firing arc limited to 45° to simulate fixed, directional flak turrets — avoid auto-tracking beyond arc.

Restricted to Capital-class defensive hardpoints — enforce requirement in Store and Fitting UI.

Consider pairing with Wildfire CIWS systems for comprehensive defense layering.

