Effect:
Medium-range guided missile launcher for Capital-class ships.
Fires heavy ordnance capable of adjusting trajectory mid-flight to pursue large or moderately agile targets.
Delivers high-impact explosive payloads with full 360° coverage, ideal for fleet defense or sustained bombardment.
Its long reload cycle and high power draw make it most effective as an alpha-strike or finisher weapon.

Upgrade Model:
Increase Damage and Range per level. Reload and Power Cost remain constant unless higher-level data indicate otherwise.

Implementation Notes:

Guided missile logic with 45°/s turn rate and 95 m/s projectile speed.

Each missile uses standard hit, crit, and armor calculations upon detonation.

Applies Power Cost at missile launch.

360° firing arc allows full-coverage targeting but should obey targeting lock rules (cannot fire through ship geometry).

Designed for anti-capital and anti-line engagements — inefficient versus Strike-class ships.

Restricted to Capital-class hardpoints — enforce requirement in Store and Fitting UI.

Consider adding missile trail and exhaust visual effects for cinematic impact.

